{"metadata": {"team_id": "necessarily", "topic_id": "1001", "run_id": "necessarily-engineering", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Geoffrey Hinton's AI Concerns", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The \u2018Godfather of AI\u2019 warns about potential dangers of the technology as he quits Google\n\nBritish-Canadian computer scientist Geoffrey Hinton admits he has fears for the future of AI\n\nIn a Frankenstein-esque tale of maker and master, Geoffrey Hinton, 75, dubbed \u2018the godfather of AI\u2019, has left Google with a parting warning over the dangers of artificial intelligence.", "citations": {"d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079": 28.0}}, {"text": "Reflecting on the effects of his work, Dr Hinton said: \u2018I console myself with the normal excuse: If I hadn\u2019t done it, somebody would have,\u2019 as he admitted, \u2018it is hard to see how you can prevent the bad actors from using it for bad things.\u2019\n\nRead More\nCyber Society: Meet the NFT duo dominating the metaverse\n\nOld Etonian digital artists Dominic Smith and Joe Carnell have caught the attention of Brooklyn Beckham, Steve Aoki and Jaden Smith\u00a0\n\nThe scientist went on to warn that AI could be taught to \u2018create sub-goals like \u201cI need to get more power\u201d\u2019, and be harnessed by nefarious actors to wreak havoc.", "citations": {"d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079": 28.0}}, {"text": "There was a New York Times tech columnist\u2019s piece about his unsettling interaction with ChatGPT in February; an open letter calling for a moratorium on AI research in March; \u201cgodfather of AI\u201d Geoffrey Hinton\u2019s dramatic resignation from Google and warning about the dangers of AI; and just this week, OpenAI CEO Sam Altman\u2019s testimony before Congress, in which he said his \u201cworst fear is we cause significant harm to the world\u201d and encouraged legislation around the technology (though he also argued that generative AI should be treated differently, which would be convenient for his company).", "citations": {"d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762": 34.0}}, {"text": "\u201cWe view the current moment similar to the beginning of the nuclear era, and we have the benefit of public perception that is consistent with the need to take action.\u201d\n\nOne nebulous aspect of the poll, and of many of the headlines about AI we see on a daily basis, is how the technology is defined.", "citations": {"d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762": 27.0}}, {"text": "Geoffrey Hinton, \u201cthe godfather of AI,\u201d recently made headlines as he left Google aft", "citations": {"2dd164a6-0781-4d60-93cd-ed77f5d0419b_204409654": 17.0}}], "references": ["d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079", "d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762", "2dd164a6-0781-4d60-93cd-ed77f5d0419b_204409654"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "necessarily", "topic_id": "1002", "run_id": "necessarily-engineering", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Geoffrey Hinton's AI Concerns", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The \u2018Godfather of AI\u2019 warns about potential dangers of the technology as he quits Google\n\nBritish-Canadian computer scientist Geoffrey Hinton admits he has fears for the future of AI\n\nIn a Frankenstein-esque tale of maker and master, Geoffrey Hinton, 75, dubbed \u2018the godfather of AI\u2019, has left Google with a parting warning over the dangers of artificial intelligence.", "citations": {"d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079": 28.0}}, {"text": "Reflecting on the effects of his work, Dr Hinton said: \u2018I console myself with the normal excuse: If I hadn\u2019t done it, somebody would have,\u2019 as he admitted, \u2018it is hard to see how you can prevent the bad actors from using it for bad things.\u2019\n\nRead More\nCyber Society: Meet the NFT duo dominating the metaverse\n\nOld Etonian digital artists Dominic Smith and Joe Carnell have caught the attention of Brooklyn Beckham, Steve Aoki and Jaden Smith\u00a0\n\nThe scientist went on to warn that AI could be taught to \u2018create sub-goals like \u201cI need to get more power\u201d\u2019, and be harnessed by nefarious actors to wreak havoc.", "citations": {"d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079": 28.0}}, {"text": "There was a New York Times tech columnist\u2019s piece about his unsettling interaction with ChatGPT in February; an open letter calling for a moratorium on AI research in March; \u201cgodfather of AI\u201d Geoffrey Hinton\u2019s dramatic resignation from Google and warning about the dangers of AI; and just this week, OpenAI CEO Sam Altman\u2019s testimony before Congress, in which he said his \u201cworst fear is we cause significant harm to the world\u201d and encouraged legislation around the technology (though he also argued that generative AI should be treated differently, which would be convenient for his company).", "citations": {"d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762": 34.0}}, {"text": "\u201cWe view the current moment similar to the beginning of the nuclear era, and we have the benefit of public perception that is consistent with the need to take action.\u201d\n\nOne nebulous aspect of the poll, and of many of the headlines about AI we see on a daily basis, is how the technology is defined.", "citations": {"d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762": 27.0}}, {"text": "Geoffrey Hinton, \u201cthe godfather of AI,\u201d recently made headlines as he left Google after a long association so he could sound the alarm about AI\u2019s ability to outsmart humans and spawn devastating problems for mankind\u2019s existence.", "citations": {"2dd164a6-0781-4d60-93cd-ed77f5d0419b_204409654": 17.0}}, {"text": "Catastrophic predictions by experts in this revolutionary field have propelled them to urge governments and technology corporations to urgently put in place regulations and guidelines to ensure that pernicious effects of AI are avoided.", "citations": {"2dd164a6-0781-4d60-93cd-ed77f5d0419b_204409654": 13.0}}], "references": ["d0d53bd7-a835-4e68-9f88-55c12fd01693_296881079", "d68ef650-26f1-4416-8554-6962b17c7d2e_697429762", "2dd164a6-0781-4d60-93cd-ed77f5d0419b_204409654"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "necessarily", "topic_id": "1003", "run_id": "necessarily-engineering", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Digital Nomads", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Featured, Features, Study Abroad\n\nA Guide for College Students Embracing the Digital Nomad Lifestyle\n\nA digital nomad is someone who works remotely and travels often.", "citations": {"4acd88c5-7d2b-4157-a17b-8edb9d9769ad_4928390": 8.0}}, {"text": "You have to learn how to balance the fun of traveling with work and school commitments.", "citations": {"4acd88c5-7d2b-4157-a17b-8edb9d9769ad_4928390": 7.0}}, {"text": "Rated 5/5 on the App Store, and featured in Digital Nomads Daily, Expedia, and Business Insider, Citizen Remote stands as the singular essential tool for navigating the lifestyle of remote work and is on sale now through Jan.", "citations": {"255cffed-9128-4d3c-aeb9-60ac4940c381_592587899": 16.0}}, {"text": "Their user-friendly web and mobile app is designed specifically for borderless remote citizens, and it offers a one-stop-shop for browsing a wide range of remote work visas available worldwide.", "citations": {"255cffed-9128-4d3c-aeb9-60ac4940c381_592587899": 9.0}}, {"text": "Spain leads the way\n\nFor UK nationals seeking relocation for a better quality of life, one country stands out as the preferred destination for remote work, with 22 per cent choosing Spain as their first option\n\nThe United States received 19 per cent of the votes and France in third place with 13 per cent.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 12.0}}, {"text": "With 46 per cent of British professionals considering relocating for remote work, the survey sheds light on this trend.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 7.0}}], "references": ["4acd88c5-7d2b-4157-a17b-8edb9d9769ad_4928390", "255cffed-9128-4d3c-aeb9-60ac4940c381_592587899", "371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127"]}
