{"metadata": {"team_id": "necessarily", "topic_id": "1019", "run_id": "necessarily-engineering", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Tai Chi & Fall Prevention", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The way it works, Nobi detects a fall\n1) After 30 seconds, Nobi will ask \"Did You Fall\"\n2) If the is answer is anything other a clear \"NO\", Nobi will alert a \u00a0family member or caregiver\n3) Nobi allows two-way communication through the lamp, making it possible for family or care staff to talk with the person on the ground, reassuring that help is on the way.", "citations": {"be9acef4-e833-4fce-bed2-7d6483b24199_159032719": 18.0}}, {"text": "Jessica Naziri has the latest innovations for older adults who are incorporating tech into their lives to improve socialization, safety while living alone, and even their physical health as they age.", "citations": {"be9acef4-e833-4fce-bed2-7d6483b24199_159032719": 11.0}}, {"text": "29 in the journal bmj.com, suggest that \"reducing the risk of falling and improving protective responses during a fall may be an important and feasible means of preventing fractures and other serious injuries in the elderly,\" the study authors wrote in a journal news release.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 16.0}}, {"text": "Most of the programs reduced fall-related injuries and appeared to significantly curb falls that lead to fractures, serious injuries and medical care.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 11.0}}, {"text": "Hoping to bring those numbers down, the Area Agency on Aging 3 hosted a \"Falls Prevention Lunch and Learn\" at Primrose Retirement Community of Lima to discuss possible fall risks and ways to prevent falls among older adults.", "citations": {"22783762-0562-4cf0-bd52-4a8a39cccb8e_409869631": 15.0}}, {"text": "Guest speaker Ashlin Toland stressed the importance of maintaining a healthy and active lifestyle, explaining how crucial it is for older adults to receive regular health testing and ensure they understand the medications they are on.", "citations": {"22783762-0562-4cf0-bd52-4a8a39cccb8e_409869631": 15.0}}], "references": ["be9acef4-e833-4fce-bed2-7d6483b24199_159032719", "184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782", "22783762-0562-4cf0-bd52-4a8a39cccb8e_409869631"]}
